{"type":"message","id":"a555a752","parentId":"a9381650","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:46:47.860Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It's 1:46 AM ET, which is within quiet hours (11pm-7am). The system message mentions an exec failed with session \"sharp-ze\". Let me check what that was about, but I should stay quiet since it's late night.\n\nLooking at the heartbeat state:\n- lastChecks all around 1742749080 (which is around 5 hours ago)\n- It's within quiet hours\n\nThe system message says \"Exec failed (sharp-ze, code 1)\" - this is a system-level notification. Since it's quiet hours and this appears to be an internal system event, I should reply HEARTBEAT_OK. The exec failure might be from a previous session or background task - nothing that requires action at 1:46 AM.","thinkingSignature":"65c55f86444ecbbb7a03ca1c3b828bd054614363199452bde9cbadee83a9e69f"},{"type":"text","text":"HEARTBEAT_OK"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":727,"output":163,"cacheRead":10875,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":11765,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774331202508}}
